  <h2 id="farm-animals">Farm Animals</h2>
  <p>Farm animal vocabulary is essential because these characters appear in many compound words, idioms, and cultural expressions. The character 牛 (niú, cow/ox) alone appears in dozens of common words.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Chinese</th><th>Pinyin</th><th>English</th><th>Related Words</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>牛</td><td>niú</td><td>Cow / Ox</td><td>牛肉 (beef), 牛奶 (milk), 牛仔 (cowboy)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>马</td><td>mǎ</td><td>Horse</td><td>马上 (immediately), 马路 (road)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>猪</td><td>zhū</td><td>Pig</td><td>猪肉 (pork), 猪年 (Year of the Pig)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>羊</td><td>yáng</td><td>Sheep / Goat</td><td>羊肉 (lamb), 山羊 (goat)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>鸡</td><td>jī</td><td>Chicken / Rooster</td><td>鸡蛋 (egg), 鸡肉 (chicken meat)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>鸭</td><td>yā</td><td>Duck</td><td>烤鸭 (roast duck), 鸭蛋 (duck egg)</td></tr>
